0%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20she's%20hearing%20directly%20from%20colleagues%20across%20various%20industries%20%E2%80%94%20shows%20that%20employees%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foxford-professor-3-ways-schools-can-teach-students-shape-ai-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eheavily%20rely%20on%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20losing%20core%20skills%20at%20a%20startling%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20tremendous%20amount%20of%20empirical%20data%20on%20this%20question%20of%20skill%20attrition%20or%20skill%20atrophy%2C%26quot%3B%20Berg%20said%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Philosopher%26quot%3B%20podcast%20this%20week.%20%26quot%3BWe%20talk%20a%20lot%20about%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20acquire%20a%20skill%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20skills%20also%20require%20maintaining%2C%20she%20said%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Berg%20did%20not%20cite%20particular%20studies%2C%20there%20is%20research%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foxford-warns-ai-making-teens-faster-but-shallower-thinkers-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOxford%20University%20Press%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20journals%2C%20including%20Springer%20and%20MDPI%2C%20that%20suggests%20AI%20may%20boost%20speed%20and%20engagement%20in%20learning%2C%20but%20often%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20depth%2C%20critical%20thinking%2C%20creativity%2C%20and%20long-term%20skill%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2240d56067-b0bd-47b8-a198-d4d76961f687%5C%22%3EAI%20could%20be%20damaging%20the%20workers%20who%20need%20to%20learn%20the%20most%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBerg%20said%20the%20workers%20most%20vulnerable%20to%20this%20deskilling%20effect%20are%20junior%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20it's%20not%20just%20a%20problem%20with%20the%20humanities%20subjects%3B%20computer%20science%20professors%20say%20that%20students%20and%20early-career%20developers%20are%20relying%20so%20heavily%20on%20AI%20tools%20that%20they're%20no%20longer%20learning%20how%20to%20write%20or%20debug%20code%20on%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20one%20thing%20for%20a%20senior%20coder%20to%20use%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20junior%20people%20are%20useless%20because%20they%20cannot%20help%20themselves%20from%20using%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20they%20lean%20on%20AI%20from%20day%20one%2C%20Berg%20said%2C%20they%20never%20build%20the%20foundational%20knowledge%20required%20to%20understand%20what%20the%20AI%20is%20doing%20%E2%80%94%20let%20alone%20verify%20or%20correct%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2269e4f420-23f3-443a-a4c6-6638471d9371%5C%22%3EAI%20is%20becoming%20a%20crutch%20%E2%80%94%20even%20outside%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBerg%20said%20AI%20dependency%20is%20spreading%20far%20beyond%20the%20workplace.%20Adults%20now%20consult%20chatbots%20for%20everything%20from%20emotional%20support%20to%20daily%20decision-making%20%E2%80%94%20a%20shift%20she%20believes%20erodes%20independent%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20majority%20%E2%80%94%20if%20not%20something%20close%20to%20%E2%80%94%20of%20AI%20use%20among%20adults%20isn't%20work-related%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20%26quot%3Bconstant%20advice%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%20of%20weird%20sociability%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bemotional%20task%20management.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20analysis%20of%201.58%20million%20ChatGPT%20conversations%20by%20researchers%20at%20OpenAI%2C%20Duke%20University%2C%20and%20Harvard%20University%20found%20that%20by%20June%202025%2C%2073%25%20of%20messages%20from%20adult%20users%20were%20non-work-related%2C%20though%20the%20study%20did%20not%20break%20down%20the%20specific%20non-work%20uses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20kind%20of%20reliance%2C%20she%20said%2C%20weakens%20the%20cognitive%20capacities%20people%20need%20not%20only%20to%20perform%20specialized%20jobs%20but%20to%20function%20independently%20in%20everyday%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223503116a-6c98-49ba-af53-678aa577e444%5C%22%3EA%20looming%20crisis%20of%20competence%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBerg's%20point%20is%20that%20AI%20doesn't%20merely%20automate%20tasks%20%E2%80%94%20it%20automates%20the%20very%20processes%20through%20which%20people%20develop%20their%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20workers%20grow%20dependent%20on%20AI%2C%20they%20lose%20the%20friction%20that%20strengthens%20their%20ability%20to%20reason%2C%20problem-solve%2C%20and%20make%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20them%20compromising%20their%20most%20basic%20levels%20of%20their%20ability%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20threat%20to%20the%20highest%20level%20of%20their%20ability%20is%20just%20tremendous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20companies%20continue%20to%20push%20AI%20into%20every%20workflow%20under%20the%20banner%20of%20efficiency%2C%20she%20said%2C%20they%20may%20end%20up%20with%20a%20generation%20of%20employees%20who%20appear%20more%20productive%20on%20paper%20but%20lack%20the%20ability%20to%20perform%20without%20digital%20hand-holding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20AI%20might%20not%20be%20enhancing%20the%20workforce.%20It%20might%20be%20slowly%20dismantling%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-tools-are-deskilling-workers-philosophy-professor-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1764412998000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69297c3889026fbb4d0e9548%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-tools-are-deskilling-workers-philosophy-professor-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20philosophy%20professor%20warns%20that%20AI%20reliance%20is%20weakening%20workers'%20judgment%2C%20creativity%2C%20and%20problem-solving.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tspirlet%40insider.com%20(Thibault%20Spirlet)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-to