e%20interview%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmedical-school-regret-tried-please-parents-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emedical%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January%202020.%20Then%2C%20life%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20grandmother%20passed.%20She%20raised%20me%2C%20so%20after%20that%2C%20I%20had%20to%20navigate%20life%20a%20little%20differently.%20I%20became%20the%20sole%20caretaker%20for%20my%20Vietnam%20War%20veteran%20grandfather%20and%20my%20intellectually%20disabled%20adult%20brother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20fall%20of%20last%20year%2C%20I%20had%20the%20wonderful%20idea%20to%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-waymo-uber-california-robotaxi-rules-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erideshare%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20supplement%20my%20income%20while%20studying%20and%20caring%20for%20my%20family.%20However%2C%20it%20has%20not%20been%20what%20I've%20planned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20I%20had%20heard%20from%20others%20who%20drove%20rideshare%20was%20that%20they%20did%20it%20full-time%20and%20were%20able%20to%20make%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20a%20week.%20But%20the%20most%20profitable%20times%20to%20work%20don't%20always%20fall%20within%20the%20hours%20I'm%20able%20to%20spend%20outside%20and%20work.%20Sometimes%20I%20have%20to%20study%20when%20lots%20of%20people%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-users-cancelling-human-driven-rides-get-waymo-taxi-atlanta-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erequesting%20rides%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20at%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20when%20I%20started%20driving%20rideshare%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-first-time-driver-learning-curve-model-y-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erented%20a%20vehicle%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20Lyft.%20It%20was%20very%20expensive%3A%20I%20